        "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
        "body": "When there is an error in executing the test script, the error message shows a simple \"Script Error\".\r\n\r\nSee https://sponge.corp.google.com/target?id=adfbbeb3-e772-404a-b263-c4edd7c4c621&target=//firebase/datastore/clients/web/testing/integration:minified_integration_tests_chrome-linux as an example.\r\n\r\nThis usually means someone on the team has to reproduce the issue and involves manual steps in figuring out what is wrong. This has cost our team lots of time in the past and I'm guessing other teams to.\r\n\r\nIf the error and stacktrace could be provided it would greatly reduce the work needed to figure out what went wrong and make fixing the bug much quicker."
